Client Layer\par
\bullet\tab The client uses a browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, etc.).\par
\bullet\tab The browser is used to send requests and receive responses.\par
\bullet\tab Users interact with the application through the browser.\par
\par
UI Layer (Presentation Layer)\par
\bullet\tab This layer is responsible for presentation logic.\par
\bullet\tab Technologies used: \par
o\tab Angular\par
o\tab React\par
\bullet\tab It handles: \par
o\tab User interface (pages, forms, buttons)\par
o\tab User input\par
o\tab Sending API requests to the backend\par
\bullet\tab It does not contain business logic or database access.\par
\par
API Layer (Business Logic Layer)\par
\bullet\tab This layer contains the core business logic.\par
\bullet\tab Frameworks used: \par
o\tab Spring Boot\par
o\tab FastAPI\par
o\tab Django\par
\bullet\tab Responsibilities: \par
o\tab Validating requests\par
o\tab Applying business rules\par
o\tab Processing data\par
o\tab Sending responses back to the UI layer\par
\bullet\tab Acts as a bridge between UI and Database.\par
Database Layer\par
\bullet\tab Used for data storage and retrieval.\par
\bullet\tab Stores: \par
o\tab User data\par
o\tab Application data\par
o\tab Transaction data\par
\bullet\tab The API layer interacts directly with the database, not the UI layer.\par
\par
Flow of the Application\par
1.\tab User performs an action in the browser\par
2.\tab Request goes to the UI layer\par
3.\tab UI sends request to the API layer\par
4.\tab API processes logic and interacts with the database\par
5.\tab Response flows back: \par
o\tab Database \f2\u8594?\f0  API \f2\u8594?\f0  UI \f2\u8594?\f0  Browser\par
\par
