Software Development Life Cycle \endash  Practical Flow Explanation\par
This cycle shows how a software requirement moves from client idea to production and maintenance.\par
\par
1. Requirements Document Phase\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab Client / Business Stakeholders\par
\bullet\tab Architect (Arch)\par
\bullet\tab Sometimes Business Analyst (BA)\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Client explains: \par
o\tab What problem they want to solve\par
o\tab What features they expect\par
\bullet\tab Requirements are shared in: \par
o\tab Text documents\par
o\tab Wireframes (screens, UI flow diagrams)\par
Output\par
\bullet\tab Requirements Document\par
\bullet\tab Clear understanding of: \par
o\tab Functional requirements\par
o\tab High level expectations\par
 This document is understood and validated by the Architect.\par
No coding happens here\par
\par
2.  Technical Design Document Phase\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab Architect (Arch)\par
\bullet\tab Technical Lead (TL)\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Requirements are converted into technical design\par
\bullet\tab Decisions are made on: \par
o\tab How many classes\par
o\tab How many interfaces\par
o\tab How many components / modules\par
o\tab Architecture pattern (monolith, microservices, etc.)\par
o\tab Technology stack\par
Output\par
\bullet\tab Technical Design Document (TDD)\par
\bullet\tab Blueprint of the application\par
 This document guides developers during coding.\par
 Still no coding\par
\par
3.  Coding Phase\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab Senior Software Engineer (SSE)\par
\bullet\tab Software Engineer (SE)\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Developers: \par
o\tab Write code based on Technical Document\par
o\tab Implement business logic\par
o\tab Follow coding standards\par
o\tab Do unit testing\par
Output\par
\bullet\tab Working code\par
\bullet\tab Features implemented as per design\par
Code is handed over to testing team.\par
4. Testing Phase\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab QA Team / Testing Team\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Testers: \par
o\tab Verify functionality\par
o\tab Find bugs and defects\par
o\tab Perform: \par
\f4\'a7\f0\tab Functional testing\par
\f4\'a7\f0\tab Regression testing\par
\f4\'a7\f0\tab Sometimes performance testing\par
Output\par
\f1\bullet\tab Bug reports (if any)\par
\bullet\tab Test results\par
\bullet\tab QA sign off (if passed)\par
 If bugs are found, code goes back to developers.\par
\par
5.\tab Deployment Phase (GO LIVE)\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab DevOps Team\par
\bullet\tab Release Team\par
\bullet\tab Sometimes Developers\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Tested code is deployed to: \par
o\tab Production Environment\par
\bullet\tab Application becomes available to end users\par
\bullet\tab This stage is called GO LIVE\par
Output\par
\bullet\tab Live application\par
\bullet\tab Users start using the software\par
\par
6.\tab Maintenance Phase\par
Who is involved\par
\bullet\tab Maintenance Team\par
\bullet\tab Support Team\par
\bullet\tab Sometimes Developers\par
What happens\par
\bullet\tab Any issues reported by users are handled\par
\bullet\tab Bug fixes\par
\bullet\tab Minor enhancements\par
\bullet\tab Performance tuning\par
Output\par
\bullet\tab Stable system\par
\bullet\tab Continuous improvements\par
 This phase continues throughout the life of the application.\par
\par
Complete Flow in One Line (Very Important)\par
Client gives requirements \f2\u8594?\f0  Architect designs \f2\u8594?\f0  Developers code \f2\u8594?\f0  QA tests \f2\u8594?\f0  Code goes live \f2\u8594?\f0  Maintenance handles issues.\par
