What is Python?\par
Python is a high level, interpreted, and general purpose programming language.\par
It is easy to learn and use because of its simple syntax and readability.\par
Python supports multiple programming paradigms such as procedural, object oriented, and functional programming.\par
It is widely used in web development, data analysis, automation, artificial intelligence, and machine learning.\par
\par
Advantages of Python\par
1.\tab Easy to Learn and Use\par
Python has simple syntax, which makes it beginner friendly.\par
2.\tab Interpreted Language\par
Code is executed line by line, making debugging easier.\par
3.\tab Large Standard Library\par
Python provides many built in libraries and frameworks.\par
4.\tab Platform Independent\par
Python programs can run on Windows, Linux, and macOS.\par
5.\tab Strong Community Support\par
Large community means more tutorials, tools, and help.\par
6.\tab Supports AI and ML\par
Python has powerful libraries like NumPy, Pandas, TensorFlow, and Scikit learn.\par
\par
How is Python useful in AI and ML World? (5 Scenarios)\par
1.\tab Data Analysis and Preprocessing\par
Python is used to clean, analyze, and prepare data using libraries like Pandas and NumPy.\par
2.\tab Machine Learning Model Development\par
Libraries such as Scikit learn help in building and training ML models easily.\par
3.\tab Deep Learning Applications\par
Python supports deep learning using TensorFlow, Keras, and PyTorch.\par
4.\tab Natural Language Processing (NLP)\par
Python is used in chatbots, language translation, and sentiment analysis using NLTK and spaCy.\par
5.\tab Computer Vision\par
Python is used for image recognition and face detection using OpenCV and TensorFlow.\par
