What is AAA Pattern?\par
AAA stands for:\par
1.\tab Arrange\par
2.\tab Act\par
3.\tab Assert\par
It is a standard structure for writing unit test cases so that tests are:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Easy to read\par
\bullet\tab Easy to understand\par
\bullet\tab Easy to maintain\par
________________________________________\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  Explanation Using Your Fan Example\par
System: Computer Fan\par
________________________________________\par
1.\tab Arrange \f1\endash  Set up the environment\par
\ldblquote Get Electricity Board \emdash  Arrange the Env\rdblquote\par
\bullet\tab You prepare everything needed before the action\par
\bullet\tab Nothing is tested here yet\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In real life:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Power supply is available\par
\bullet\tab Fan is properly connected\par
\bullet\tab Switch is off\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In unit testing:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Create objects\par
\bullet\tab Initialize variables\par
\bullet\tab Set test data\par
________________________________________\par
2.\tab Act \endash  Perform the action\par
\ldblquote Switch the button on \emdash  Take Action\rdblquote\par
\bullet\tab You perform one specific action\par
\bullet\tab This is the behavior you want to test\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In real life:\par
\f1\bullet\tab You turn ON the switch\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In unit testing:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Call the method/function being tested\par
________________________________________\par
3.\tab Assert \endash  Verify the result\par
\ldblquote Check whether the fan is rotating or not\rdblquote\par
\bullet\tab You verify the outcome\par
\bullet\tab This decides if the test passes or fails\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In real life:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Fan rotates \f2\u8594?\f0  \f3\u9989?\f0  Test passed\par
\f1\bullet\tab Fan does not rotate \f2\u8594?\f0  \f3\u10060?\f0  Test failed\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  In unit testing:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Compare expected output with actual output\par
\par
\par
\f5\u-10179?\u-8903?\f0  AAA Pattern in Python Unit Test (Example)\par
Python\par
def test_add():\par
# Arrange\par
a = 2\par
b = 3\par
\par
# Act\par
result = add(a, b)\par
\par
# Assert\par
assert result == 5\par
Show more lines\par
Mapping:\par
\f1\bullet\tab Arrange \f2\u8594?\f0  prepare inputs\par
\f1\bullet\tab Act \f2\u8594?\f0  call add(a, b)\par
\f1\bullet\tab Assert \f2\u8594?\f0  check result\par
